8th March, the time when the International Women's Day is celebrated worldwide to acknowledge the incredible and bold achievements by women, 
Addery spotted some tiny rays of rainbow near their store in Andheri West! 

Let's hear the story of Anupama Srivastav who is embarked on a selfless journey of teaching students from the poor strata of society for whom quality education is only accessible in their dreams. 

Her wise wisdom is a voice of every women who works consistently to give a new perception to selflessness!

We request you all to forward this to everyone near you, those who aren’t getting the education they deserve. To make this world a better place! 

You can also DM us to get the contact details for the NGO, to support them in any way you deem fit!

latestPosts.caption:
Behind every post, there's a story you don't see.
As a brand, we rarely speak about the challenges that come with collaborations.
But this time, we felt the need to share not for drama, but for dialogue.

We recently faced a situation where our trust was taken for granted.
Despite agreements and follow-ups, our products were not returned, and only after legal action did things move.

And sadly… this isn’t the first time.
We’ve seen how quickly behaviour changes after the “free stuff” is secured.

🤍 This post is a reminder:
Professionalism isn’t optional.
Collabs deserve clarity.
And trust shouldn’t come with fine print.

#adderyfashionhouse #addery #fashionstyle #fashionphotography #fypage #fashionblogger #fyp #fashion #trending #trend #trendingreels #swimming #shopnow #styleblogger #swimsuit #swimwear #swimmingpool #swimsuits #summer #swimwearfashion
latestPosts.alt: Photo by ADDERY on July 16, 2025. May be a graphic of text that says 'The other side of Content creation'.

childPosts.alt: Photo by ADDERY on July 16, 2025. May be a graphic of text that says 'The other side of Content creation'.

Photo by ADDERY on July 16, 2025. May be an image of turban, poster, magazine and text that says 'Behind every viral reel, every dreamy aesthetic shoot, and every "seamless" collaboration, there's a lot that happens behind the scenes. And not all of it is as perfect as it looks. On May 24, we collaborated with Ritu Singh- @babelicious_indiana for a content shoot. We sourced multiple outfits, coordinated timelines, and shared our brand vision trusting that the other side would energy and effort. match our What followed left us questioning more than just the collab.'.

Photo by ADDERY on July 16, 2025. May be an image of text that says 'As per our agreement, the pieces were to be returned within a week. But that didn't happen. We followed up. Called. Messaged. Reminded. For an entire month after the promised return date, we kept reaching out patiently, respectfully hoping she would keep her word. But each day brought a new excuse... until the replies stopped altogether. We were left with no choice but to file a police complaint. Only then, on the second day after the complaint, the products were sent back.'.

Photo by ADDERY on July 16, 2025. May be a doodle of text that says 'It left us wondering... Why is it so difficult for people to carry out their part of the agreement? When did commitment become optional? When did words start losing their value? As a brand, we give a lot-time, creativity, products, energy. gy. And at the bare minimum, we expect mutual respect and responsibility. But even after a month of follow-up even after legal action, even after the products were returned- No content was never delivered. Not a sin single reel. Not a sin single post. Not even a thank you. This wasn't a collaboration. It was a one-sided transaction.'.
Photo by ADDERY on July 16, 2025. May be a Twitter screenshot of text.

Photo by ADDERY on July 16, 2025. May be a meme of text that says 'The same person who was warm and enthusiastic suddenly becomes cold and dismissive. It hurts not just because of the delayed returns or the silence but because of the shift in respect, energy, and intent. You wanted the product for free. You got it. But where's the follow-through? Where's the professionalism? This pattern isn't just disappointing it's exhausting. And unfortunately, we know we're not alone in facing it.'.

Photo by ADDERY on July 16, 2025. May be a graphic of text that says 'We're not here to to name name, shame, or spread negativity. We're here to talk about what small businesses and brands silently go through. Collaborations should be a space for creativity, respect, and reliability'.

Photo by ADDERY on July 16, 2025. May be a graphic of text that says 'We're not against creators. We love collaborating with genuine people who value creativity, effort, and trust as much as we do. :But experiences like this force us and others like us to pause and ask: When did free products become more important than professional responsibility? When did "collab" stop meaning collaboration? Brands aren't just supply machines. We're people. We put in work we communicate, we plan and we expect the same energy back. Let's create a space where ethics matter just as much as aesthetics.'.
